3:**Complexity:** Complex · **Phase:** Production · **Estimated Cost:** ~$1,500–6,000/month depending on infusion center size and scheduling volume
15:The numbers are striking. A typical infusion chair costs a health system $500,000 to $1 million per year when you factor in space, equipment, staffing, and overhead. Running at 60% utilization instead of 80% means you're effectively burning $200,000 per chair per year. A 30-chair center leaving 20% on the table is wasting $6 million annually. And that's before you count the patient experience cost of 2-hour waits, the pharmacy waste from poor timing coordination, and the nursing overtime from schedules that pile everyone into the same 3-hour window.
220:| Cost Estimate | ~$1,500/month (small center, 15 chairs) to ~$6,000/month (large center, 50+ chairs, real-time optimization) |
